  "texts": [
    "One aim of generating this dataset was to quantify how often the expected relationships and directionalities occur, to provide concrete evidence in this so-far theoretical debate with only anecdotal evidence available.",
    "We began by testing the basic hypothesis that CRISPR and ORF reagents targeting the same gene should yield negatively correlated (opposite) profiles to each other.",
    "Surprisingly, we found that the CRISPR and ORF profiles are slightly positively correlated with each other, in both cell types (Fig. 5a and Supplementary Table 3).",
    "We then compared the cosine similarities between compound-CRISPR pairs and compound-ORF pairs that target the same gene.",
    "In both U2OS and A549 cells, we found that both compound-CRISPR and compound-ORF pairs were more positively correlated than negatively correlated (Fig. 5b and Supplementary Table 4)."
